 for bestpractices and # Comments, Mentions & Collaboration

## Overview
Implement a comprehensive threaded comments, mentions, and collaboration system that supports decisions workflows for Archject. This includes threaded decision discussions with user mentions and attachments, real-time updates, email notifications, and admin moderation. The system powers three connected pages: Decision Detail Page, Notifications Center, and Client Portal (No-Login Link). The goal is a visually calm, highly usable interface that prioritizes clarity, audit trails, and effortless client approvals while enabling internal teams to collaborate efficiently.

---

## Components to Build

1) Decision Detail Page (page_decision_detail)
- Purpose: Full view of a Decision Card with visual option comparisons, threaded comments, status, history, attachments, and actionable controls.
- Subcomponents:
  - Decision Card Header: Title, project/phase context, status badge (Published, Pending, Rejected), last updated timestamp.
  - Visual Comparison Panel: Side-by-side option cards with thumbnails, materials, finishes, prices, trade-offs; ability to select preferred option as “approved” or to create a comparison view.
  - Comments Thread
    - Thread container with hierarchical (threaded) comments.
    - Mentionable users with @ syntax, searchable user picker, and inline user avatars.
    - Attachments: File upload (images, PDFs, specs), attachment list within comments, drag-and-drop support.
    - Resolve/Flag: Per-comment resolved toggle and admin flag for moderation.
  - Attachments Gallery: Centralized attachments for the decision (drawings, specs, PDFs).
  - History & Audit Log: Chronological timeline of actions (created, updated, comments added, approvals, attachments added, status changes) with timestamps and user attribution.
  - Actions Bar:
    - Share Decision (generate shareable link and/or export summary)
    - Export (PDF/CSV/Decision Log)
    - Create Follow-up Task (integrates with internal tasking)
    - Approve/Decline Controls (with optional comments)
  - Mentions & Notifications Trigger: Real-time highlight of mentions in the thread; inline notification preferences for mentions.

2) Notifications Center (page_notifications)
- Purpose: Centralized view of all in-app and email notifications, with per-user settings.
- Subcomponents:
  - Notification Feed: Real-time/up-to-date list of reminders, approvals, comments, mentions, and status updates. Filters (All, Mentions, Reminders, Approvals, Comments, System).
  - Notification Settings:
    - In-app notification toggles per event type (Reminders, Approvals, Comments, Mentions)
    - Email notification toggles per event type
    - Scheduling preferences (time windows, daily digest)
    - Do-not-disturb periods
  - Quick Actions: Mark all as read, mute thread, configure delivery channels.
  - Notification Detail Drawer/Modal: Expanded view for a single notification with context and quick action anchors (reply, follow-up task, or open related decision).

3) Client Portal (No-Login Link) (page_client_portal)
- Purpose: Mobile-first client-facing view accessible via secure, tokenized link. Clients review Decision Cards, compare options, comment, and approve; no account required.
- Subcomponents:
  - Secure Access View: Tokenized URL handling, one-time link validation, auto-expire if unused after X days.
  - Decision Card Overview: Visual comparison, option highlights, and high-level summary (costs, timeline, trade-offs).
  - Commenting Interface: Lightweight threaded comments (anonymous client identity with tokenized name), mention support for internal stakeholders (via internal user mapping), attachment support.
  - Approval Controls: Approve/Request Changes with optional client notes; digital signature/pseudo-approval indicator.
  - Attachment & Reference Material: View/download materials related to the decision.
  - Progress & Audit: Lightweight activity feed showing client interactions for the decision, timestamps.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech Stack: Choose between React (with hooks) or Vue, maintain consistency with existing stack. Use WebSocket or Server-Sent Events for real-time updates.
- UI Components:
  - Card, Button, Tabs, Drawer/Modal, Avatar, Icon Button, Tag/Badge, Timeline, Comment Thread, Attachment Uploader, File Preview, Search Bar, Dropdown, Tooltip, Snackbar/Toast.
- Pages & Routes:
  - /decision/:decisionId (Decision Detail)
  - /notifications (Notifications Center)
  - /client-portal/:token (Client Portal)
- Interactions:
  - Real-time updates: Live comment additions, status changes, new attachments, and new mentions update in-app UI instantly.
  - Mentions: Recognize @username syntax; render as interactive mention chips; clicking opens user profile or attendee card; trigger in-app notification and optional email.
  - Attachments: Drag-and-drop, progress indicators, size/type validation, streaming previews (image/video/pdf thumbnails).
  - Moderation: Admins can flag comments, mark as resolved, delete if necessary, and view audit trails.
  - Accessibility: Keyboard navigability, ARIA roles, high-contrast focus states, screen reader labels.
- Performance:
  - Debounced search, pagination or infinite scroll for large comment threads, efficient diff rendering for updates.
  - Optimize for mobile with responsive breakpoints; mobile-first interactions for client portal.

### Backend
- Tech Stack: Preferred language/stack aligned with existing services (Node.js/Express or NestJS, Python Django/FastAPI, or similar).
- Data Models:
  - User: id, name, email, avatar, role (admin, designer, client, staff), preferences for notifications.
  - Decision: id, projectId, title, description, status, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy, attachments list, options[].
  - Option: id, decisionId, name, description, thumbnail, attributes (materials, finishes), priceEstimate.
  - Comment: id, decisionId, parentCommentId (nullable), authorId, text, mentions[] (userIds), attachments[] (attachmentIds), createdAt, updatedAt, resolved boolean, status (active/hidden/reported).
  - Attachment: id, fileName, mimeType, size, url, uploadedBy, uploadedAt, relatedEntity (decision/comment/attachment metadata).
  - Mention: id, commentId, mentionedUserId, createdAt, notifiedViaEmail boolean.
  - Notification: id, userId, type (mention, comment, reminder, approval), relatedDecisionId, message, isRead, createdAt, payload.
  - ActivityLog: id, decisionId, actionType (create/update/comment/attachment/approval), actorId, details, timestamp.
  - FollowUpTask: id, decisionId, assignedToUserId, title, dueDate, status, createdAt, updatedAt.
  - ReviewSettings (for client portal): token, expiresAt, allowedActions, clientIdentityNameMapping.
- APIs & Services:
  - Comment API
    - POST /decisions/:decisionId/comments
    - GET /decisions/:decisionId/comments (with pagination)
    - PUT /comments/:commentId (update text, resolve)
    - DELETE /comments/:commentId (moderation)
  - Attachment API
    - POST /decisions/:decisionId/attachments
    - GET /attachments/:attachmentId
  - Mentions & Notifications
    - POST /notifications/mention (triggered on comment)
    - GET /notifications?userId=&filters=
    - POST /notifications/read (mark as read)
  - Decision & Option API
    - GET /decisions/:id
    - POST /decisions/:id/approve
    - POST /decisions/:id/compare (set active option or comparison)
    - POST /decisions/:id/share
    - POST /decisions/:id/export
  - Client Portal Auth
    - GET /client-portal/validate?token=
  - Real-time
    - WebSocket endpoint /ws for decisionId channels; fall back to SSE if WebSocket not available
- Validation & Business Rules:
  - Attachments: Max size per file, allowed MIME types; virus/malware scanning hook.
  - Mentions: Validate user exists; avoid mentioning non-participants; rate-limit mention notifications.
  - Comment: Require non-empty text; sanitize content; filter disallowed content.
  - Moderation: Admins can flag and resolve content; audit trail updated.
  - Notifications: Respect user preferences; suppression settings on Do Not Disturb.
  - Client Portal: Token-based access only; read-only unless client actions enabled (comment/approve) through token scope.

### Integration

- Data Consistency:
  - Use a centralized CQRS/Events approach or adopt consistent RESTful CRUD with optimistic UI updates.
  - Ensure comment creation triggers: attachment association, mention extraction, notification enqueue, and real-time broadcast.
- Real-time Sync:
  - Broadcast via WebSocket to subscribed clients (Decision Detail page, Notifications Center, Client Portal) on:
    - New comment
    - Comment update (resolve)
    - New attachment
    - Status/decision updates
  - Fallback: SSE if WebSocket unavailable; periodic polling as last resort.
- Email Delivery:
  - Email templates for mentions, approvals, reminders, and follow-ups with secure, per-user unsubscribe options.
  - Rate limits on email notifications to prevent spamming.
- Security & Access Control:
  - Role-based access: Admin, Designer, Client, Viewer (read-only where appropriate).
  - Client Portal uses tokenized links with restricted scopes; no login required.
  - Data ownership and export: Ensure exports include full decision logs with timestamps and authors.

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Decision Detail Page
- User opens a Decision from a project workspace.
- View shows the Decision Card with visual comparison of options on top.
- User reads status, reviews history, and opens the Comments thread.
- User mentions a teammate: types @username, selects from dropdown; recipient receives in-app and optional email notification.
- User uploads attachments to a comment; attachments appear inline with the comment.
- Real-time update: When a teammate replies, the new comment appears instantly without manual refresh.
- User can resolve a comment or flag it; moderators can review flagged content.
- User clicks Approve/Decline; optionally adds a note; if approved, the decision status updates and triggers related workflows (e.g., follow-up tasks, client notification).
- User uses Share or Export to generate a decision summary in PDF/CSV; can share a link or export data to contracts.
- User creates a Follow-up Task linked to the decision; task appears in the internal task panel.

2) Notifications Center
- User navigates to Notifications Center; sees a chronological feed of all activity related to decisions they participate in (mentions, approvals, reminders, comments).
- User updates preferences to enable/disable in-app and email for specific event types.
- User marks notifications as read; bulk actions supported; can filter by type.

3) Client Portal (No-Login Link)
- Client receives a tokenized link (email or direct share); link opens a token-validated, time-limited portal.
- Client views the Decision Card with side-by-side option comparisons, notes, and visual cues.
- Client comments on the decision with optional attachments; mentions trigger internal notifications as needed.
- Client approves or requests changes directly in the portal; actions recorded with timestamp and client identity mapped from token.
- Client can download attachments and view all relevant decision materials.
- Portal restricts access to the specific decision(s) included in the token; audit trail logs all client interactions.

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details summarized]
- users(id, name, email, role, avatar, notificationPrefs)
- decisions(id, projectId, title, description, status, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy, attachments)
- options(id, decisionId, name, description, thumbnailUrl, attributes)
- comments(id, decisionId, parentCommentId, authorId, text, createdAt, updatedAt, resolved, status, attachments)
- attachments(id, fileName, mimeType, size, url, uploadedBy, uploadedAt, relatedEntityType, relatedEntityId)
- mentions(id, commentId, mentionedUserId, createdAt, deliveredVia)
- notifications(id, userId, type, relatedDecisionId, message, isRead, createdAt, payload)
- activityLogs(id, decisionId, actionType, actorId, details, timestamp)
- followUpTasks(id, decisionId, assignedToUserId, title, dueDate, status)
- clientTokens(token, expiresAt, decisionId, allowedActions, clientNameMapping)

API Endpoints: (RESTful design)
- GET /decisions/{decisionId}
- POST /decisions/{decisionId}/comments
- GET /decisions/{decisionId}/comments
- PUT /comments/{commentId}
- DELETE /comments/{commentId}
- POST /decisions/{decisionId}/attachments
- GET /attachments/{attachmentId}
- POST /decisions/{decisionId}/approve
- POST /decisions/{decisionId}/share
- POST /decisions/{decisionId}/export
- POST /notifications/mentions (triggered after comment creation)
- GET /notifications
- POST /notifications/read
- GET /client-portal/validate?token={token}
- POST /client-portal/comments (with token)
- POST /client-portal/approve (with token)

Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth for internal users; tokenized access for client portal.
- Authorization: Role-based access control (RBAC) with explicit scopes per endpoint.
- Data validation: Server-side input validation, content sanitization, file type/size validation.
- Rate limiting: Per-user per-endpoint throttling for comment posting and attachments.
- Logging: Audit logs for all critical actions (comments created/edited, approvals, status changes, moderation actions).

Validation
- Frontend:
  - Required fields: decision title, at least one option selected for approval, non-empty comment text when posting.
  - Attachments: size/type validation; success/failure UX with progress bars.
  - Mentions: proper user lookup, no self-mention in certain contexts, immediate in-app notification.
- Backend:
  - Referential integrity: decisionId, commentId references must exist.
  - Attachments must be linked and retrievable.
  - Email notifications respect user preferences and suppression times.
  - Token-based client portal access expires as configured.

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Real-time updates: Comments, attachments, status changes update across all connected clients (Decision Detail, Notifications Center, Client Portal) within 1–2 seconds.
- [ ] Mentions trigger in-app and email notifications according to user preferences; mentions render correctly with clickable user previews.
- [ ] Threaded comments support nested replies with proper indentation, collapse/expand, and resolve/flag controls for admin.
- [ ] Attachments upload, preview, and download work securely; validation enforces size/type constraints.
- [ ] Admin moderation tools function: flag, resolve, and delete with audit trail and user attribution.
- [ ] Client Portal: Tokenized link grants access to the specific decision; clients can comment and approve; no login required; actions are audited and visible to internal users.
- [ ] Exports: PDF/CSV export contains full decision data, options, comments (with mentions), attachments metadata, and audit logs.
- [ ] Accessibility: All interactive elements accessible via keyboard, with ARIA labels and proper focus management.

---

## UI/UX Guidelines

Apply the project's design system to ensure consistency with Archject brand.

Visual Style and Layout
- Color Palette
  - Primary background: #F7F7F9
  - Secondary background: #FFFFFF
  - Accent: #0052CC
  - Neutrals: #E5E7EB, #D1D5DB, #6B7280, #111827
  - Status: #10B981, #F59E42, #EF4444
- Typography
  - Font family: Modern geometric sans-serif (Inter, SF Pro, etc.)
  - Headings: H1 ~28px, H2 ~22px, H3 ~18px; weight 600–700
  - Body: 15–16px, line-height ~1.5–1.6
- Layout
  - 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters
  - Generous whitespace; left-aligned content
- Components
  - Cards: White with subtle shadow, 8–12px radius, dividers in #E5E7EB
  - Buttons: Primary filled (#0052CC) with white text; secondary ghost/outline
  - Inputs: Rounded, borders #D1D5DB, focus ring on active
  - Avatars, icons: Monochrome with active-state fill
  - Badges: Rounded pills colored by status
- Interactions
  - Hover states: Subtle lift or tint
  - Transitions: Smooth, micro-interactions for focus and hover
  - Microcopy: Clear, concise, action-oriented

Design Philosophy
- Modern, calm, professional aesthetic
- Clarity, simplicity, and quick scanning
- High readability, consistent hierarchy and predictable interactions
- Seamless cross-device experience (desktop + mobile)

